Kenyan health workers prepare for cases of the new coronavirus at the Mbgathi District hospital in Nairobi. Photographer: Simon Maina/AFP via Getty Images Photographer: Simon Maina/AFP via Getty Images Sign up to our Next Africa newsletter and  follow Bloomberg Africa on Twitter Kenya reported its first case of the coronavirus, a 27-year-old female national who had returned from the U.S. via London, Health Secretary Mutahi Kagwe said on Friday in a televised speech. “The case was confirmed on the 12th of March,” he said in the capital, Nairobi. “The patient is stable, her temperature has gone down to normal.”